BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:07ffae25f8eafd321a5056e3bf9e2443
SUMMARY:Service Design Global Conference 2026 (SDGC26)
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261028
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261030
LOCATION:Frankfurt RheinMain region, Wiesbaden (RheinMain Congress Center) and online
DESCRIPTION:Quelle: https://www.servicedesignglobalconference.com/\nThe Service Design Global Conference 2026 (SDGC26) takes place 28-30 October in the Frankfurt RheinMain region, both onsite at the RheinMain Congress Center in Wiesbaden and online. This event aims to discover how service design drives innovation and transforms modern organizations. The theme, 'Beyond Boundaries: Enabling Solutions That Shape Tomorrow,' explores moving past limits to shape resilient, meaningful futures through service design. The program includes workshops, an SDN Members Event, conference days with speakers, and networking opportunities.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ab0aa9c15394862cc8023099d808ae27
SUMMARY:Digitale Leute Summit 2026: Germany's leading cross-functional conference for Product, Engineering, and UX/Design.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261117
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261118
LOCATION:Cologne, Germany (AI Deep Dive Day at Smartvillage Cologne, Conference Day at Palladium Cologne)
DESCRIPTION:Quelle: https://digitale-leute.de/summit/\nThe Digitale Leute Summit 2026 is a two-day event focused on software product development, with a strong emphasis on UX/Design. Day 1, the AI Deep Dive Day (November 17 at Smartvillage Cologne), offers a bootcamp-style experience on practical AI application across product, design, and engineering workflows. Day 2, the Conference Day (November 18 at Palladium Cologne), features international speakers, talks, interviews, panels, and masterclasses, providing insights into tools, tactics, and methods for developing better digital products for professionals in UX Design, Product, and Engineering.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:87031da64cf63f1095b85b94bd7d5514
SUMMARY:Service Design (SD) Conference Europe
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260608
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260612
LOCATION:London
DESCRIPTION:Quelle: https://www.assistkd.com/news/article/service-design-conference-agenda-now-live\nMomentum is gathering in the run up to the Service Design (SD) Conference Europe, as IRM UK launches the live agenda and announces the first speakers. The Service Design conference, co-founded by IRM UK and AssistKD in 2025, will take place in London from 8th to 12th June 2026. It will be co-located with the Enterprise and Business Architecture (EBA) Conference Europe and the Business Change and Transformation (BCT) Conference Europe (BCT), bringing together the worlds of architecture, transformation and service design. Jonathan Hunsley (AssistKD) and Victoria Banner (Royal London Group) will be holding a workshop on the afternoon of Wednesday June 10th on the topic of introducing service frameworks to enhance clarity, standards, and collaboration across the change ecosystem. For the conference agenda and how to book, please follow this link: https://irmuk.co.uk/2026/02/eba-bct-sd-conference-europe-2026-speakersarticle/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:8980df12c88db009ee932e4bc1b3180f
SUMMARY:Service Design Conference Europe 2026
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260608
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260612
LOCATION:Convene 133 Houndsditch, London; etc.venues Fenchurch Street, London
DESCRIPTION:Quelle: https://irmuk.co.uk/service-design-award-2026/\nJoin us at the Service Design Conference Europe 2026, co-located with the Business Change & Transformation Conference and the Enterprise & Business Architecture Conference. This unique trio of events offers a transformative experience, redefining your understanding of Enterprise Architecture, Business Architecture, Service Design, Design strategies, and Business Change & Transformation.
END:VEVENT
