UID:9b763d9731e8a021982a72c10e942eed
SUMMARY:Gamification in Fintech: From Boosting Engagement to Becoming a Lovemark
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260128
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260128
LOCATION:Online
DESCRIPTION:Quelle: https://www.interaction-design.org/literature/article/ux-conferences-calendar?srsltid=AfmBOoo7C52rsF4XF7bJf9V98RwciZt2UUcVgVzIdHmi-fQWPg5wZaUE\nCraft Innovations holds a session to explore how gamification impacts product goals, like retention, feature adoption, transaction frequency, loyalty, and more. Ideal for Product Managers in fintech and banking; UX / CX designers working on complex products; founders building consumer or B2B fintech solutions; innovation, growth, and digital teams.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:03bdd37d584f8df1c2d46a92ea447085
SUMMARY:AWE Asia 2026
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260202
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260204
LOCATION:Singapore and online (Singapore Expo)
DESCRIPTION:Quelle: https://www.interaction-design.org/literature/article/ux-conferences-calendar?srsltid=AfmBOoo7C52rsF4XF7bJf9V98RwciZt2UUcVgVzIdHmi-fQWPg5wZaUE\nAWE Asia is the region's leading annual conference for the Extended Reality (XR) industry, spanning Augmented Reality (AR), Virtual Reality (VR), and related Metaverse technologies. It brings together XR enterprise adopters, solution providers, developers, investors, creators, governments, and media. The conference includes two days of thought-provoking sessions, extensive networking opportunities, and an expo. Ideal for AR, XR, and VR practitioners.
END:VEVENT
